    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="witness" subtype="poem" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" rhyme="aa">
                <head type="title"><handShift new="#HANDJR1833-34" script="cursive" medium="ink"/>The <del type="strikethrough">descent</del> Summit<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="the_summit_poem_glosses_contextual.php#THESUMMITPASSINGTHEALPSCLUSTER"/></head>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>Oh we are on the mountain top</l>
                    <l>The clouds float by in fleecy flock</l>
                    <l>Heavy and dank, Around below</l>
                    <l>A wilderness of turf and snow</l>
                    <l>Scanty rock turf, or <del type="strikethrough">sandstone</del><add place="above"><space unit="chars" n="15"/>marble</add> bare<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">700</add></l>
                    <l>Without a living thing, for there</l>
                    <l>Not a bird clove the thin cold air</l>
                    <l>With labouring wing, the very goat</l>
                    <l>To such a height ascendeth not</l>
                    <l>And if the clouds thick drapery<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">705</add></l>
                    <l>Clove for a moment, you would see</l>
                    <l><subst><del type="strikethrough">A</del><add>The</add></subst> long white snowfields on each side</l> 
                    <l>Clasping the mountain breast, or heaped</l>
                    <l>In high wreathed hills whence torrents leaped</l>
                    <l>And gathering force, as down<del type="strikethrough">ward</del><add place="above"><space unit="chars" n="23"/>they</add> well<del type="strikethrough">ing</del><add rend="linenumber-right-JR">710</add></l>
                    <l>To aid the <del type="strikethrough">broad</del><add place="above"><space unit="chars" n="12"/>swift</add> <geogName corresp="#RHINE">Rhine</geogName>s headlong swell</l>
                    <l>And <del type="strikethrough">and</del>here and there a mouldring cross</l>
                    <l>Of dark pine matted oer with moss</l>
                    <l>Hung oer the precipice, to tell</l>
                <pb facs="MSVIII59v"/>
                    <l>Where some benighted traveller fell.<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">715</add></l>
                    <l>Or where the avalanches leap</l>
                    <l>Hurled down with its wild thunder sweep</l>
                    <l>Him unexpecting, and to pray</l>
                    <l>The passing traveller to stay</l>
                    <l>And looking from the precipice,<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">720</add></l>
                    <l>Dizzily down <del type="strikethrough">from</del><add place="above"><space unit="chars" n="15"/>to</add> the abyss</l>
                    <l>To wing to heaven one short prayer</l>
                    <l>One, for the soul that parted there.</l>
                    <l>I thought as, by the cross I past</l>
                    <l>Of far <geogName corresp="#HELVELLYN">Helvellyn</geogName>s dreary waste<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">725</add></l>
                    <l>Mid my own hills, and legend strange,<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="the_summit_poem_glosses_contextual.php#GOUGH"/></l>
                    <l>How from dark <geogName corresp="#STRIDINGEDGE">Striden</geogName>s ridgy range,<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="the_summit_poem_glosses_contextual.php#STRIDINGEDGE"/></l>
                    <l>One fell, upon a wintry day</l>
                    <l>When snow wreaths white concealed his way</l>
                    <l>And died, beside a <placeName corresp="#REDTARN">small dark tarn</placeName><ref type="gloss_contextual" target="the_summit_poem_glosses_contextual.php#REDTARN"/><add rend="linenumber-right-JR">730</add></l>
                    <l>Oerlooked by crags, whose foreheads stern</l>
                    <l>Shut in a little vale, a spot</l>
                    <l>By man unknown and trodden not</l>
                    <l>Green, and most beautiful, and lay,</l>
                    <l>His bones there whitening many a day,<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">735</add></l>
                    <l>Though sun and rain might work their will</l>
                    <l>From bird and wolf protected still</l>
                    <l>For he had one companion, one,</l>
                    <l>Watched oer him in the desert lone</l>
                    <l>That faithful dog beside sat aye,<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">740</add></l>
                    <l>Baying the vulture from his prey,<ref type="gloss_textual" target="the_summit_poem_glosses_textual.php#SUNANDRAIN" /></l>
                    <l>Else moved not, slept not, stirred not, still,</l>
                    <l>Oer lake and mountain, rock and hill</l>
                    <l>Rung his short plaintive timid cry<ref type="gloss_textual" target="the_summit_poem_glosses_textual.php#TIMIDCRY" /></l>
                <pb facs="MSVIII60r"/>
                    <fw type="pageNum" place="top-right"><handShift new="#HANDWGC" medium="pencil"/>60</fw>
                    <l><handShift new="#HANDJR1833-34" script="cursive" medium="ink"/>Most melancholy, None passed by,<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">745</add></l>
                    <l>None &#x2038;<add place="above"><space unit="chars" n="6"/>heard</add> his sorrowing call for aid</l>
                    <l>Yet still beside the corse he staid</l>
                    <l>And watched it moulder, and the day</l>
                    <l>When three long months had past away</l>
                    <l>It was discovered where it lay<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">750</add></l>
                    <l>And he beside it. Would that, we could love</l>
                    <l>As he did.<ref type="gloss_textual" target="the_summit_poem_glosses_textual.php#LOVEASHEDID" /></l>
                </lg>
            </div>
